         <abstract>
            <p>This note demonstrates that the Lewellen, Long, and McConnell (LLM) lease valuation model can be expanded to include tax shield borrowing opportunities that are embodies in Myers, Dill, and Bautista's model. Although both models produce the same conclusions about the net advantage of leasing, the expanded LLM model can be applied in more cases.</p>
